// ============================================================================
// NS Smoothness: Riemann-Liouville Fractional Derivative Axioms
// ============================================================================
//
// QUESTION: Do the explicit formulas for fractional derivatives
// (Riemann-Liouville, Caputo, Grünwald-Letnikov) provide axioms
// that close the ½-derivative gap?
//
// Three axioms extracted from the RL integral representation:
//
//   1. KATO-PONCE (Fractional Leibniz):
//      ||D^s(fg)|| ≤ C(||D^s f||·||g||_∞ + ||f||_∞·||D^s g||)
//      Applied to stretching: S² ≤ C² · H32³
//      (Sharper than S ≤ grad_v_inf · Ω when H32 large)
//
//   2. FRACTIONAL GRONWALL:
//      D^{1/2}_t Ω ≤ C·Ω^{3/2} at critical exponent p = 1+α = 3/2.
//      Mittag-Leffler bound: Ω(t) ≤ Ω₀ · E_{1/2}(C√Ω₀·√t).
//      Exponential growth (bounded on [0,T]), NOT finite-time blow-up.
//
//   3. FRACTIONAL POINCARÉ:
//      H32² ≥ Ω² (RL lower bound tighter than H32 ≥ Ω)
//
// ============================================================================
// Z3 RESULTS (each test in its own file to avoid axiom contamination):
//
//   File                        Test                          Result
//   ──────────────────────────  ────────────────────────────  ──────
//   ns_rl_kato_ponce.kleis      Kato-Ponce + blow-up          SAT
//   ns_rl_gronwall.kleis        Frac Gronwall + blow-up       SAT
//   ns_rl_combined.kleis        ALL RL axioms + blow-up       SAT
//   ns_rl_standard_sobolev.kleis  Standard α=1 + growth       SAT
//   ns_rl_hyper_base.kleis      Hyperviscous base (no growth) SAT
//   ns_rl_hyperviscous.kleis    Hyperviscous α=5/4 + growth   UNSAT ★
//
// ============================================================================
// THE CRITICAL AXIOM (what Lions 1969 really proved):
//
//   Standard NS (α=1):                 Hyperviscous (α=5/4):
//   grad_v_inf ≤ H32                   grad_v_inf² ≤ P54
//   ↓                                  ↓
//   H32 NOT controlled by              P54 IS the dissipation
//   dissipation (P)                    → Sobolev bound absorbed
//   → GAP                             → NO GAP
//
//   The SINGLE axiom that differs:
//     α=1:   Sobolev connects ∇v to H^{3/2} (not dissipation)
//     α=5/4: Sobolev connects ∇v to P_{5/4} (IS dissipation)
//
// ============================================================================
// CONPARIAN INTERPRETATION:
//
//   The Riemann-Liouville formula does NOT close the gap.
//   Kato-Ponce, fractional Gronwall, and fractional Poincaré
//   are all EQUIVALENT representations of the same structural
//   obstruction. They provide different views of the gap:
//
//   - Interpolation: H32 sits between Ω and P, not controlled
//   - Kato-Ponce: S ~ H32^{3/2}, but dissipation ~ P ≠ H32
//   - Fractional Gronwall: critical exponent p = 1+α = 3/2 exactly
//   - Lions threshold: need α ≥ 5/4 (extra ¼ in the Laplacian)
//
//   The gap is ½ derivative because:
//     • H^{3/2} is the Sobolev threshold for L^∞(∇v) in 3D
//     • Dissipation provides H² (= H^{3/2 + 1/2})
//     • H^{3/2} ≠ H² (not the same, can't absorb)
//     • Need H^{5/2} (= H^{3/2 + 1}) for absorption → α = 5/4
//
//   This is not a failure of fractional calculus tools.
//   The RL formula REVEALS the gap is structural,
//   not a matter of choosing the right derivative definition.
// ============================================================================
